The paper deals with the joint optimization of beamforming and power control in a distributed antenna system, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of network assistant full-duplex (NAFD) and the optimization of uplink and downlink rates also suggest the relevance of these sub-categories.
